  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\n\r\nWhile working on #6246 we found out that the current approach to detect if we are running all `EthereumTests` is brittle: we first copy the test specifications (`.json` files) from the git submodule into the .NET build output folder as resources, and then using reflection we verify that all test specifications have a corresponding C# test suite.\r\n\r\nThe problem with this approach is that we might forget to update the `.csproject` file thus not copying all the test specifications (see: https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/pull/6246/files/1121c62f6c2d423a4575877c46f933ed54987ad2#diff-676a290f2c8070406b94cb7c652de3b10e76fc6114caf865c3e60d4d22001785)\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nThe solution should not require any manual intervention when it comes to detecting missing C# tests. Ideally, we would have a C# test that performs this verification.\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered**\r\n- Keep things as they are.\r\n- Create a separate tool that performs this verification (ex. a bash script) which could be used in CI.\r\n",
